# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Peerbot instance created with `@peerbot/cli` v{{CLI_VERSION}}

## Quick Start

```bash
# Start the bot
npx peerbot dev

# View logs
npx peerbot logs

# Stop the bot
npx peerbot down
```

## Configuration

### Environment Variables

Edit `.env` to configure:
- `SLACK_BOT_TOKEN` - Your Slack bot token
- `SLACK_APP_TOKEN` - Your Slack app token
- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` - Your Anthropic API key
- `PEERBOT_PUBLIC_GATEWAY_URL` - Public URL for OAuth callbacks

### Worker Customization

{{#if CUSTOMIZE_WORKER}}
Edit `Dockerfile.worker` to add custom tools and dependencies. Changes are automatically detected and rebuilt when running `peerbot dev`.

Example customizations:
```dockerfile
# Add system packages
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y postgresql-client

# Add Python packages
RUN pip install pandas matplotlib

# Add Node.js packages
RUN bun add @octokit/rest
```
{{else}}
To customize the worker, run:
```bash
npx peerbot customize
```

This will create a `Dockerfile.worker` file you can edit.
{{/if}}

### Advanced Configuration

Edit `peerbot.config.js` for advanced settings:
- Resource limits (CPU, memory)
- Volume mounts
- Platform-specific overrides
- Custom environment variables

## Deployment

### Local Development (Docker)

```bash
npx peerbot dev
```

### Production Deployment

#### Kubernetes
```bash
npx peerbot deploy --target kubernetes
```

#### AWS ECS
```bash
npx peerbot deploy --target ecs
```

#### Cloudflare Containers
```bash
npx peerbot deploy --target cloudflare
```

## Commands

- `peerbot init` - Initialize a new Peerbot project
- `peerbot dev` - Start development server
- `peerbot logs [service]` - View logs
- `peerbot down` - Stop all services
- `peerbot rebuild` - Rebuild worker image
- `peerbot deploy [--target]` - Deploy to production

